# Rollout History & Rollback

Each rollout = a new ReplicaSet = a numbered revision.

```bash
kubectl rollout history deployment/web
kubectl rollout history deployment/web --revision=2
```

## Roll back — one command

```bash
kubectl rollout undo deployment/web
kubectl rollout undo deployment/web --to-revision=1
```

> `undo` is **just another rollout** — makes a *new* revision matching the old template. After undo: revisions 1, 2, **3** (3 = 1).

## Pause / resume — batch risky changes

```bash
kubectl rollout pause deployment/web
# ...several edits...
kubectl rollout resume deployment/web   # ships as ONE rollout
```

## Breadcrumbs

```bash
kubectl annotate deployment/web \
  kubernetes.io/change-cause="bump nginx 1.28 (CVE)"
```

> The **history of ReplicaSets** makes "go back to last week" one command.
